<subSubSection id="C30663EAFFB96C69FF624339A76EF934" pageId="15" pageNumber="1322" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA33061FFB96C69FF624339A76EF934" blockId="15.[130,777,1565,1775]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1322">
DIAGNOSIS. — Protoconch multispiral. Teleoconch squat to moderately elongate, obconic shells with broad and rounded shoulders. Spire whorls low to very low, smooth, convex. Subsutural flexure very shallow in small species - deep in larger species, moderately curved and moderately asymmetrical. Colour pattern consists mainly of spirally arranged spots and dashes in continuous spiral rows (Diagnosis followingTucker &amp; Tenorio (2009) and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D4D90FFB96C69FD9A439BA76AF934" author="HARZHAUSER M. &amp; LANDAU B." pageId="15" pageNumber="1322" pagination="1" refId="ref18832" refString="HARZHAUSER M. &amp; LANDAU B. 2016. - A revision of the Neogene Conidae and Conorbidae (Gastropoda) of the Paratethys Sea. Zootaxa 4210 (1): 001 - 178. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4210.1.1" type="journal article" year="2016">Harzhauser &amp; Landau (2016)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30663EAFFB96C69FF624235A247F9F7" pageId="15" pageNumber="1322" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA33061FFB96C69FF624235A69BF8F1" blockId="15.[131,775,1810,2028]" box="[132,232,1810,1836]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1322">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA33061FFB96C69FF624216A247F9F7" blockId="15.[131,775,1810,2028]" lastBlockId="15.[813,1455,1491,1581]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1322">
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D4D90FFB96C69FF624216A7F6F897" author="PUILLANDRE N. &amp; BOUCHET P. &amp; DUDA T. F. &amp; KAUFERSTEIN S. &amp; KOHN A. J. &amp; OLIVERA B. M. &amp; WATKINS M. &amp; MEYER C." box="[132,389,1841,1868]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1322" pagination="290 - 303" refId="ref20786" refString="PUILLANDRE N., BOUCHET P., DUDA T. F., KAUFERSTEIN S., KOHN A. J., OLIVERA B. M., WATKINS M. &amp; MEYER C. 2014. - Molecular phylogeny and evolution of the cone snails (Gastropoda, Conoidea). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 78: 290 - 303. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2014.05.023" type="journal article" year="2014">
Puillandre 
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFB96C69FF184215A741F890" box="[254,306,1841,1867]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1322">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4BE2FFB96C69FDEF4216A40EF890" authorityName="da Motta" authorityYear="1991" box="[521,637,1841,1867]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Kalloconus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="1322" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFB96C69FDEF4216A40EF890" box="[521,637,1841,1867]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1322">Kalloconus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at subgenus level and found a monophyletic group. Today 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4BE2FFB96C69FD764276A575F8B0" authorityName="da Motta" authorityYear="1991" box="[656,774,1873,1899]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Kalloconus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="1322" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFB96C69FD764276A575F8B0" box="[656,774,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1322">Kalloconus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the tropical East Atlantic (West Africa), but its fossil record demonstrates that it also had a European distribution during the Miocene in the Proto- Mediterranean and Paratethys. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4BE2FFB96C69FE1F42F6A4A6F837" authority="" authorityName="da Motta" authorityYear="1991" box="[505,725,2001,2028]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="1322" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Kalloconus">
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFB96C69FE1F42F6A44DF830" box="[505,574,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1322">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFB96C69FDB442F6A4B9F830" box="[594,714,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1322">Kalloconus</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4BE2FFB96C69FBC840F4A343FA36" authority="" box="[1070,1328,1491,1517]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="1322" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Monteiroconus">
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFB96C69FBC840F4A201FA36" box="[1070,1138,1491,1517]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1322">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFB96C69FB6240F3A356FA36" box="[1156,1317,1492,1517]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1322">Monteiroconus</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
, mainly by the lack of spiral cords on the whorls and by its straight, lightly concave whorls.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
